This paper discusses the development of a modular end-to-end relation extraction system for slot filling, which involves techniques from natural language processing, information retrieval, machine learning, and database systems. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to the intersection of computer science and linguistics. 

The paper also mentions the use of distant supervision classifiers, which are a type of weakly supervised learning method commonly used in information extraction tasks. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper discusses the importance of query expansion using a translation model based on Wikipedia links, which is a technique commonly used in database systems and information retrieval. This suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category.
